    <briefdescription>
<para>Structure to define the HW dependencies of a keyboard status. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Because the rows and columns GPIO ports and pins are variable-length arrays depending on the keyboard layout, <bold>double pointers</bold> are used to define GPIOs (because GPIOs are defined as pointers of GPIO_TypeDef type) and <bold>pointers</bold> are used to define the arrays of rows and columns. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
